      "rank": "GENUS",
      "description": "True crocodiles. The most sophisticated living reptiles and the closest relatives of birds. Despite their ancient lineage — over 250 million years — they show complex parental care, social communication, and even tool use. Fourth tooth of lower jaw is visible when mouth is closed — distinguishing them from alligators.",
